1
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,980
Episode 19

2
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,680
Count them carefully.

3
00:01:47,760 --> 00:01:48,760
You got it wrong before.

4
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:49,920
Okay.

5
00:01:51,070 --> 00:01:51,920
Birthday? No.

6
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,510
I've got a shipment to get out.

7
00:01:54,590 --> 00:01:55,560
Come on!

8
00:01:56,120 --> 00:01:57,400
This is the new millennium.

9
00:01:57,790 --> 00:01:58,640
Gao Xiang says

10
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,280
a birthday at the millennium

11
00:02:00,280 --> 00:02:01,150
has to be celebrated.

12
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,120
(You've already missed two birthdays.)

13
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:05,560
(I came from Shenyang for this!)

14
00:02:05,950 --> 00:02:07,560
Alright.

15
00:02:08,870 --> 00:02:10,400
Remember the stall

16
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:11,560
where we used to sing

17
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,240
with Qian?

18
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:13,520
Let's go there.

19
00:02:25,590 --> 00:02:26,840
Is Gao Xiang coming or not?

20
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:27,590
Gao Xiang! Here!

21
00:02:27,840 --> 00:02:28,360
Hey!

22
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:29,150
Boss!

23
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,630
One more seat, please.

24
00:02:30,800 --> 00:02:31,190
Okay!

25
00:02:31,590 --> 00:02:32,280
Who else?

26
00:02:32,630 --> 00:02:33,870
A mutual friend of ours.

27
00:02:34,430 --> 00:02:35,590
A mutual friend?

28
00:02:38,470 --> 00:02:39,360
Mr. Xu!

29
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:41,360
I wouldn't dare be late

30
00:02:41,470 --> 00:02:42,430
to your birthday.

31
00:02:42,870 --> 00:02:43,560
Oh, welcome!

32
00:02:43,630 --> 00:02:44,310
Have a seat.

33
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:46,080
I got you drunk,

34
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,560
and Xiang ignored me for two years.

35
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,280
Gao Xiang,

36
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:52,280
why did you get Mr. Xu to come?

37
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,430
I volunteered.

38
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,710
And I brought booze.

39
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:57,430
Here.

40
00:02:57,910 --> 00:02:58,750
Let me pour you some.

41
00:02:59,030 --> 00:02:59,840
You shouldn't have!

42
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:01,960
I have to

43
00:03:02,190 --> 00:03:03,080
pour it myself.

44
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,960
To show my respect.

45
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,240
I should be the one

46
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,590
thanking you.

47
00:03:08,750 --> 00:03:09,360
Actually,

48
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:11,150
the bank knew you got scammed.

49
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:14,030
But you paid it back

50
00:03:14,750 --> 00:03:16,190
on your own.

51
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:17,470
Someone like you

52
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:18,430
deserves respect.

53
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:19,680
And you've

54
00:03:19,710 --> 00:03:21,280
built yourself a solid reputation.

55
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,520
The credit department

56
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:23,560
is fully committed.

57
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,840
Whatever you wanna do,

58
00:03:26,120 --> 00:03:28,430
we'll give you our full support.

59
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:30,280
Good!

60
00:03:30,470 --> 00:03:31,310
Thanks, Mr. Xu.

61
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,120
Thank you.

62
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,430
He really asked to come himself.

63
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:38,080
No need to be formal.

64
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:39,080
He's my best friend.

65
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:40,000
Just call him Xu.

66
00:03:40,190 --> 00:03:41,630
Yeah, call me Xu.

67
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:42,710
That's not right.

68
00:03:43,870 --> 00:03:45,080
Come on, Fang Wanzhi.

69
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:46,400
All of us here

70
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:47,680
wish you a happy birthday!

71
00:03:48,030 --> 00:03:49,360
Thank you.

72
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,080
Happy birthday!

73
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:52,870
Mr. Xu,

74
00:03:53,030 --> 00:03:53,910
a toast to you.

75
00:03:54,470 --> 00:03:56,630
Thank you for coming.

76
00:03:56,630 --> 00:03:57,710
Sure. Happy birthday.

77
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,560
Thanks.

78
00:04:01,280 --> 00:04:02,430
No need to thank me.

79
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:03,470
My pleasure.

80
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,470
Gao Xiang, you're so thoughtful.

81
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:10,750
Just take a tiny sip.

82
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:13,310
Take care of yourself.
Don't work too hard.

83
00:04:20,830 --> 00:04:21,800
Happy birthday.

84
00:04:22,480 --> 00:04:24,720
Here's to us getting better every year.

85
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,870
(Tonight,)

86
00:04:35,240 --> 00:04:36,120
(I wanna sing a song)

87
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,310
(to someone.)

88
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:38,680
(She's irreplaceable)

89
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,310
(in my life.)

90
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,950
(Today is her birthday.)

91
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:46,240
(Wish her happiness and joy.)

92
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:52,070
♪If we could have our
first meeting again♪

93
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:56,070
♪I'd still be the me you met♪

94
00:04:56,240 --> 00:04:59,190
♪On that day♪

95
00:04:59,430 --> 00:05:03,240
♪If we could have our
first meeting again♪

96
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:06,190
♪A pot of light wine♪

97
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:12,190
♪Who cares how full the cups are♪

98
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:17,160
♪I still remember that
very first meeting♪

99
00:05:18,310 --> 00:05:20,160
♪I was all smiles♪

100
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:23,630
♪Greeting the chill in your eyes♪

101
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:27,240
♪Time has drifted through♪

102
00:05:27,360 --> 00:05:30,120
♪Years of ups and downs♪

103
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:36,800
♪Yet the years have woven a warm shawl♪

104
00:05:38,310 --> 00:05:43,160
♪We've been through wind and rain♪

105
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:46,800
♪All the colors in the world♪

106
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:49,560
♪Can't paint away our troubles♪

107
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:53,160
♪They say mountains stretch,
rivers run far♪

108
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:56,070
♪Yet water easily breaks♪

109
00:05:56,190 --> 00:06:02,040
♪But you say the gentle rain
carries your longing♪

110
00:06:18,270 --> 00:06:19,680
Qian is singing that for you.

111
00:06:21,270 --> 00:06:22,160
I know.

112
00:06:39,270 --> 00:06:40,870
We haven't been in touch for years.

113
00:06:41,870 --> 00:06:43,160
She's suddenly back in Shenzhen.

114
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,950
Don't know how she's doing.

115
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,160
Her singing there means

116
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:50,950
she's not hiding.

117
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:51,920
She's here now.

118
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:53,510
She might

119
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,560
come to us in a few days.

120
00:06:54,630 --> 00:06:55,750
Then we'll just

121
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:56,430
ask her.

122
00:06:58,510 --> 00:06:59,160
Right.

123
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,870
Lately, for some reason,

124
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:04,190
she's been on my mind.

125
00:07:04,950 --> 00:07:06,120
I'm worrying about her.

126
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:08,630
But she seems

127
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:11,120
to be doing well.

128
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:13,680
Worry more about yourself.

129
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,480
Will you graduate this year?

130
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,920
Of course.

131
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:18,120
I'm totally getting

132
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,120
my vocational diploma.

133
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,070
And I applied for college.

134
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:24,560
What's your plan?

135
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:25,870
Our loan

136
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:26,950
is finally paid off.

137
00:07:27,630 --> 00:07:28,240
It's time

138
00:07:28,270 --> 00:07:29,680
to get your diploma.

139
00:07:31,390 --> 00:07:32,920
It's been a few years since we started

140
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:33,750
at Dongmen.

141
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:35,310
We were just drowning in debt.

142
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:37,950
But now that it's cleared,

143
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:39,560
I actually have an idea.

144
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:41,870
I wanna

145
00:07:41,870 --> 00:07:43,190
rethink my career.

146
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,070
What's your take?

147
00:07:44,630 --> 00:07:45,800
I'll listen to you.

148
00:07:46,750 --> 00:07:48,040
What are you smiling at?

149
00:07:49,310 --> 00:07:49,870
Go to sleep.

150
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,190
These five years,

151
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,720
you've gained a lot,

152
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:07,600
but also missed out on a lot.

153
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:08,870
Well,

154
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,240
Shenzhen now has

155
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:11,630
a new talent market.

156
00:08:11,920 --> 00:08:13,560
Many foreign companies are hiring there.

157
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,720
Forget about the pay.

158
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,800
That was your ticket

159
00:08:16,870 --> 00:08:18,040
into a global company.

160
00:08:18,240 --> 00:08:19,270
But you missed it.

161
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:19,950
What's more,

162
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:21,360
with a bachelor's degree

163
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:23,000
and two years' work here,

164
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,270
you can get residency.

165
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,560
You didn't finish college.

166
00:08:26,270 --> 00:08:27,480
So you missed it too.

167
00:08:29,510 --> 00:08:31,310
I'm here to exercise,

168
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:32,120
not to get

169
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,630
a lecture.

170
00:08:33,790 --> 00:08:35,030
Hard truths are hard to hear.

171
00:08:35,270 --> 00:08:37,150
New millennium, new chances.

172
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,600
Let me

173
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,080
give you some real advice.

174
00:08:43,150 --> 00:08:43,630
Please.

175
00:08:44,510 --> 00:08:45,840
I'll be blunt then.

176
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,320
You can ignore all this

177
00:08:51,360 --> 00:08:53,030
if you want,

178
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:56,030
but I thought it through for you.

179
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:57,270
You gotta appreciate that.

180
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:03,080
What wonderful scenery.

181
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:05,120
I want sashimi-style dumplings.

182
00:09:05,360 --> 00:09:07,390
Can you go get some?

183
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:09,510
Sure.

184
00:09:10,360 --> 00:09:11,480
You're really going?

185
00:09:13,510 --> 00:09:14,510
Tired of me?

186
00:09:14,510 --> 00:09:15,480
Kidding me again?

187
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:40,270
Now, Shenzhen

188
00:09:40,390 --> 00:09:41,480
is booming

189
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:42,550
with opportunities.

190
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:44,550
You should find

191
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,600
a better platform

192
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:47,480
to spread your wings.

193
00:09:48,240 --> 00:09:50,000
You can't just chase short-term gains

194
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:51,510
and be a small vendor forever.

195
00:09:51,870 --> 00:09:53,030
Your dad has bigger hopes

196
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,080
for you.

197
00:09:55,480 --> 00:09:56,320
Fang Wanzhi,

198
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,320
don't waste this era.

199
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,200
Don't let yourself down.

200
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:04,480
(Orders and modern management
from Hong Kong, China,)

201
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:05,630
(and overseas)

202
00:10:06,150 --> 00:10:07,840
(play a significant role)

203
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,440
(in Shenzhen's development.)

204
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:12,120
(If I want to start from scratch,)

205
00:10:12,510 --> 00:10:14,510
(every step has to be solid.)

206
00:10:15,270 --> 00:10:17,000
(Shenzhen taught me not to complain,)

207
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,960
(but to make every stumble)

208
00:10:18,960 --> 00:10:20,320
(a stone in your moat.)

209
00:10:21,080 --> 00:10:22,550
(I chose this sea,)

210
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:25,750
(so I must sail among the reefs.)

211
00:10:26,870 --> 00:10:27,960
(Thank you)

212
00:10:28,030 --> 00:10:29,510
(for the chance to interview today.)

213
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,000
I attended college,

214
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,910
but I didn't get my degree.

215
00:10:33,510 --> 00:10:34,360
The reason is...

216
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:35,240
Skip it.

217
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:38,200
You provided the proof of your studies.

218
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:39,670
We've had

219
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:41,320
many candidates with fake diplomas.

220
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:43,550
Their diplomas aren't
as reliable as this.

221
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:45,750
Thanks, Ms. Yao.

222
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:47,000
Don't thank me.

223
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:48,720
I'm not the real interviewer.

224
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,550
Our president,

225
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:51,720
Yan Ziwei,

226
00:10:51,870 --> 00:10:52,960
will interview you.

227
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:54,120
Come with me.

228
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:06,790
President Yan.

229
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:10,630
What's this?

230
00:11:11,670 --> 00:11:13,510
Proof that she attended college.

231
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:14,600
Issued by the school.

232
00:11:14,870 --> 00:11:16,120
It's trustworthy.

233
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:17,840
I see.

234
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:41,960
Why didn't you finish your college?

235
00:11:44,670 --> 00:11:45,870
A multinational company

236
00:11:45,910 --> 00:11:46,840
like Hongtu Trading

237
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,870
doesn't fixate on diplomas, right?

238
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,000
And the job posting

239
00:11:51,150 --> 00:11:52,240
doesn't mention that.

240
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:55,600
How will you convince me to hire you?

241
00:11:57,630 --> 00:11:58,840
I've had many jobs,

242
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:00,510
run my own business,

243
00:12:00,790 --> 00:12:02,320
and opened up markets nationwide.

244
00:12:02,550 --> 00:12:03,390
I made money,

245
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,480
lost money,

246
00:12:04,790 --> 00:12:05,510
and got cheated.

247
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:06,670
Being fooled

248
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:08,480
made me more careful.

249
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,200
Just right for an assistant.

250
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:13,600
People who've been bosses
all have ambition.

251
00:12:14,910 --> 00:12:16,480
We don't need ambition here.

252
00:12:20,480 --> 00:12:21,600
If I had no ambition,

253
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:24,240
I wouldn't have applied to your company.

254
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:25,910
To be honest,

255
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:26,870
I'm seeking

256
00:12:26,870 --> 00:12:28,030
the opportunity

257
00:12:28,150 --> 00:12:28,840
to learn and grow

258
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,320
within a great company.

259
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:31,390
Absolutely,

260
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,360
I will also

261
00:12:32,390 --> 00:12:33,600
balance my personal goals

262
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:35,200
with my work responsibilities.

263
00:12:36,030 --> 00:12:37,000
Please trust me.

264
00:12:39,030 --> 00:12:40,870
President Yan, do you have
any more questions?

265
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:42,030
No.

266
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:43,720
You may go.

267
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,670
You didn't go for a job.

268
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,600
You were just having fun.

269
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,480
If I were your boss,

270
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,750
I wouldn't hire you.

271
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:06,360
I have an idea.

272
00:13:06,790 --> 00:13:07,790
Just forget

273
00:13:08,320 --> 00:13:09,790
the job search.

274
00:13:09,910 --> 00:13:11,200
Let's keep working together.

275
00:13:11,670 --> 00:13:13,080
Business isn't

276
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:14,030
as good as it was.

277
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:15,000
But we've already

278
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:17,120
paid off our loan.

279
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:19,480
Everything we make now is pure profit.

280
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:21,510
Juan,

281
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,510
Shenzhen is full of opportunities now.

282
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,720
I don't want to waste this era.

283
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,390
And I don't want to fail myself.

284
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:30,120
I want to reach higher.

285
00:13:30,670 --> 00:13:31,790
The position I applied for

286
00:13:31,870 --> 00:13:33,360
is assistant to the president.

287
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:34,480
At a large company,

288
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:36,000
that's a top-tier job.

289
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:38,000
I'll learn the company's structure

290
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,080
and operations.

291
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,480
That would be invaluable

292
00:13:40,550 --> 00:13:41,910
for our future.

293
00:13:42,790 --> 00:13:44,320
If this company doesn't hire me,

294
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:45,720
I'll apply to the next one.

295
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:46,750
I'll find one.

296
00:13:47,670 --> 00:13:48,200
Juan,

297
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:50,240
